                    h4(data-title="Impact") Impact
                    p Most photo proofing tools are built around rating images funneling thumbnails into higher rankings until the thumbnails can be compared. That's not how clients actually make decisions — they need to see similar images together as large as possible. I designed and built a self-hosted comparison tool from scratch to solve that gap, using AI-assisted prototyping to go from concept to shipped production tool in 2 days.
                    ul
                        li Existing proofing platforms charged $200–300/year for a viewing experience that hadn't evolved in years — so I built a replacement that solved the actual problem
                        li No instructions needed — clients opened a link and started choosing images for retouching without any guidance
                        li Clients were making those comparisons themselves and arriving with confident, exportable selections
                        li Retouching cart upsells converted directly from the selection flow — clients purchased additional services without a separate sales conversation
                        li Unsolicited purchase interest from other photographers confirmed this is a market gap, not just a personal workflow problem

